  "prompt": "Which are the best website for coding competition?",
  "response": "There are several highly-regarded websites for coding competitions that cater to a range of skill levels and interests. Some of the top ones include:\n\n1. **HackerRank:** Offers a variety of programming challenges across different domains and also hosts regular competitions.\n2. **Codeforces:** Known for its competitive programming contests held frequently, with active user participation and community support.\n3. **LeetCode:** Focuses on algorithmic challenges and often hosts contests, particularly popular for coding interview preparation.\n4. **TopCoder:** One of the oldest and most prestigious competitive programming platforms, offering regular Single Round Matches (SRMs).\n5. **CodeChef:** An Indian-based platform that offers monthly contests and a vibrant community of programmers.\n6. **AtCoder:** A Japanese platform that's gaining international popularity for its high-quality contests.\n7. **Kick Start by Google:** A series of coding competitions offering challenges devised by Google engineers.\n8. **HackerEarth:** Provides a variety of challenges, hackathons, and competitions along with a recruitment platform.\n9. **UVa Online Judge:** Offers a vast collection of algorithmic problems and hosts periodic contests.\n10. **CS Academy:** Features regular contests with well-designed algorithmic problems for competitive programmers.\n\nEach platform has its own unique features and community, so it's worth exploring a few to find which one best suits your interests and skill level.",
